{"id":"quant-ph/0101043","submitter":"ChuanFeng Li","authors":"Peng Xue, Chuan-Feng Li, and Guang-Can Guo (University of Science and\n  Technology of China)","title":"Efficient quantum key distribution scheme with nonmaximally entangled\n  states","comments":"5 Pages, No Figure","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A 64 (2001) 032305.","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.64.032305","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We propose an efficient quantum key distribution scheme based on\nentanglement. The sender chooses pairs of photons in one of the two equivalent\nnonmaximally entangled states randomly, and sends a sequence of photons from\neach pair to the receiver. They choose from the various bases independently but\nwith substantially different probabilities, thus reducing the fraction of\ndiscarded data, and a significant gain in efficiency is achieved. We then show\nthat such a refined data analysis guarantees the security of our scheme against\na biased eavesdropping strategy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Jan 2001 02:44:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
